SIMPLE: interosculant
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interosculant
<hw>In`ter*os"cu*lant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Mutually touching or intersecting; <as>as, <ex>interosculant</ex>
circles</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Uniting two groups; -- said of
certain genera which connect family groups, or of species that connect
genera. See <er>Osculant</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interosculate</ent>⟦br⟧
